==English==
===Etymology===
Old French from Germanic
===Noun===
'''guide'''
# someone who [[lead]]s, [[direct]]s, [[advise]]s or [[show]]s the [[way]]
# someone [[employed]] to show people around a [[place]] or an [[institution]] and offer [[information]] and [[explanation]]
# a [[document]] or [[book]] that offers information or [[instruction]]
# a [[sign]] that guides people, or a [[device]] that guides part of a machine

====Translations====
*Czech: [[průvodce]]
*Japanese: [[案内]]
*Italian: [[guida]]
*Spanish: [[guía]]
*{{pt}}: guia

===Verb===
'''to guide''' (''transitive'')
# to serve as a guide for someone or something
# to [[steer]] or [[navigate]] a [[ship]] etc, especially as a [[pilot]]
# to [[supervise]] the [[education]] or [[training]] of someone
'''to guide''' (''intransitive'')
# to act as a guide

